@startuml sequence-render-frame
'
' iDaVIE Sub-team 3 — Rendering Engine
' Sequence diagram: one rendered frame in the refactored architecture
' Team Alpha | Cache Me If You Can | Sprint 2 | 2026-06-02
'
' Source: revised_design_document.md §4 + refactoring-examples/team3/
' Participants match the AFTER classes — class-after.puml + VolumeRenderCoordinator.cs
'
' 8-step sequence: MB shell → camera → foveation → voxel offsets →
'   state assembly → shader sync (mask + uniforms) → render pass → GPU
'

title One Rendered Frame — Refactored Architecture\n<size:10>(VolumeRendererBehaviour → VolumeRenderCoordinator.Update())</size>

skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

skinparam participant {
  BackgroundColor #D6EAF8
  BorderColor     #2471A3
}
skinparam actor {
  BackgroundColor #FDFEFE
  BorderColor     #BDC3C7
}
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor              #2471A3
  LifeLineBorderColor     #7FB3D3
  GroupBorderColor        #1ABC9C
  GroupBodyBackgroundColor #F0FFFC
  NoteBackgroundColor     #FEF9E7
  NoteBorderColor         #F39C12
}

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  PARTICIPANTS
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
actor "Unity Engine\n(player loop)" as Unity

box "iDaVIE.Rendering — Unity adapter" #EBF5FB
  participant "VolumeRenderer\nBehaviour\n<size:9>[MonoBehaviour shell]</size>" as VRB
end box

box "iDaVIE.Rendering — domain layer" #F0FFF4
  participant "VolumeRender\nCoordinator" as VRC
  participant "IVolumeCameraDriver\n<size:9>(VolumeCameraDriver)</size>" as VCD
  participant "IFoveatedSamplingPolicy\n<size:9>(FoveatedSamplingPolicy)</size>" as FSP
  participant "IVolumeTexture\nManager" as VTM
  participant "IVolumeMaterial\nBinder\n<size:9>(VolumeMaterialBinder)</size>" as VMB
  participant "IMaskMode\n<size:9>(active strategy)</size>" as MM
end box

box "Cross-team contracts" #FFF8F0
  participant "IGazeProvider\n<size:9>[Sub-team 4]</size>" as GP
  participant "IRenderPipeline\n<size:9>(UrpRenderPipeline /</size>\n<size:9>HdrpRenderPipeline)</size>" as RP
end box

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  ENTRY — Unity calls VolumeRendererBehaviour
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
Unity -> VRB : Update()
activate VRB

note right of VRB
  <b>T-02 trade-off:</b> VolumeRendererBehaviour
  is the ONLY class permitted to extend
  MonoBehaviour. Zero domain logic lives here —
  it forwards the call immediately.
end note

VRB -> VRC : Update()
activate VRC

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  STEP 1 — Camera state
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
note over VRC, VCD
  <b>Step 1 — Camera state</b>
  [FIXED V-10 DIP] Coordinator never calls transform or Camera APIs directly.
  VolumeCameraDriver is the only class that reads UnityEngine.Camera.
end note

VRC -> VCD : ComputeFrame()
activate VCD
VCD --> VRC : CameraFrameState\n<size:9>(LocalToWorld, AverageIntensityProjection,\nFrustumPlanes, ProjectionMatrix)</size>
deactivate VCD

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  STEP 2 — Foveated sampling parameters
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
note over VRC, FSP
  <b>Step 2 — Foveated sampling parameters</b>
  [FIXED V-07 DIP] No direct SteamVR call in the domain. FSP reads IGazeProvider
  and returns a plain value struct — no hardware dependency escapes the policy class.
end note

VRC -> FSP : ComputeParameters()
activate FSP

  alt IGazeProvider.IsGazeAvailable == true
    FSP -> GP : GetGazeDirection()
    activate GP
    GP --> FSP : Vector3 gazeDirection\n<size:9>(normalised world-space)</size>
    deactivate GP
    FSP --> VRC : FoveationParameters\n<size:9>(StepsLow, StepsHigh, InnerRadius,\nOuterRadius, Jitter, FoveationActive=true)</size>
  else gaze unavailable <size:9>(HMD absent / init window / no eye-tracking)</size>
    FSP --> VRC : FoveationParameters.Uniform\n<size:9>(UniformSampleStep — INV-01 preserved)</size>
  end

deactivate FSP

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  STEP 3 — Mask voxel offsets (private — no external call)
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
note over VRC
  <b>Step 3 — ComputeMaskVoxelOffsets()</b> <i>[private — no external participant]</i>
  Derives four voxel-corner world-space vectors from CameraFrameState.LocalToWorld.
  [FIXED V-10 DIP] Uses the Matrix4x4 returned in Step 1; never calls transform.
end note

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  STEP 4 — Assemble VolumeRenderState (private — no external call)
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
note over VRC
  <b>Step 4 — BuildRenderState()</b> <i>[private — no external participant]</i>
  Combines CameraFrameState + FoveationParameters + RendererParameters
  into a single VolumeRenderState value struct.
  Zero heap allocation — struct copy only. NFR-08 hot-path budget preserved.
end note

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  STEP 5 — Texture rebind check
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
note over VRC, VTM
  <b>Step 5 — Texture rebind check</b>
  Textures are uploaded once at startup (or on crop / region load, not per frame).
  Per-frame: coordinator checks for a pending rebind flag only.
end note

VRC -> VTM : CurrentDataTexture, CurrentMaskTexture
activate VTM

  alt texture rebind pending <size:9>(crop changed / first load)</size>
    VTM -> VTM : GenerateCroppedVolumeTexture()\n<size:9>or GenerateVolumeTexture()\n— enforces 368 MB budget + FilterMode.Point (INV-03, INV-04)</size>
    VTM --> VRC : Texture3D (dataCube), Texture3D (maskCube)\n<size:9>[updated — coordinator forwards to BindDataTexture / BindMaskTexture]</size>
  else texture is current <size:9>(normal per-frame path)</size>
    VTM --> VRC : Texture3D (dataCube), Texture3D (maskCube)\n<size:9>[cache hit — no GPU upload]</size>
  end

deactivate VTM

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  STEP 6 — Shader uniform sync (all property writes in one place)
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
note over VRC, VMB
  <b>Step 6 — Shader uniform sync</b>
  The ONLY call path in the architecture that writes Material properties.
  Replaces 25+ scattered SetFloat/SetInt/SetVector calls in the monolith's Update().
end note

VRC -> VMB : Tick(in VolumeRenderState)
activate VMB

  '  6a — AIP keyword via pipeline adapter
  VMB -> RP : SetPipelineKeyword("SHADER_AIP", aip)
  activate RP
  note right of RP
    URP: per-material LocalKeyword
    HDRP: equivalent local keyword
    Domain never knows which.
    [FIXED V-15 Prot. Variations]
  end note
  RP --> VMB
  deactivate RP

  '  6b — Scaling / colour-map uniforms
  VMB -> VMB : PushScalingUniforms()\n<size:9>SetFloat ×6: bias, contrast, alpha, gamma, threshMin, threshMax</size>

  '  6c — Foveation uniforms (values from FoveationParameters via VolumeRenderState)
  VMB -> VMB : PushFoveationUniforms()\n<size:9>SetInt ×2: _StepsLow, _StepsHigh\nSetFloat ×3: _FovStart, _FovEnd, _FovJitter</size>

  '  6d — Mask mode strategy  [replaces the if/else chain — OCP fix]
  VMB -> MM : Apply(material, maskCube)
  activate MM
  note right of MM
    <b>[FIXED V-04 OCP]</b>
    ApplyMaskMode    → _MASK_APPLY,   α=1.0
    InverseMaskMode  → _MASK_INVERSE, α=1.0
    IsolateMaskMode  → _MASK_ISOLATE, α=0.15
    DisabledMaskMode → no keyword,    α=0.0
    New mode = new class; zero existing files change.
  end note
  MM --> VMB : <size:9>(keyword set, _MaskTex bound, _MaskAlpha pushed)</size>
  deactivate MM

  '  6e — Region highlight + vignette uniforms
  VMB -> VMB : PushHighlightUniforms()\n<size:9>SetVector ×2: _HighlightMin/Max\nSetFloat: _SaturateFactor\nSetFloat ×3: vignette params</size>

  VMB --> VRC : <size:9>(all uniforms synced, textures bound)</size>
deactivate VMB

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  STEP 7 — Enqueue render pass
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
note over VRC, RP
  <b>Step 7 — Enqueue render pass</b>
  [FIXED V-14 GRASP Indirection] Replaces Graphics.DrawProceduralNow (line 1148/1154)
  and OnRenderObject (line 1142) — both incompatible with URP.
  Domain schedules via CommandBuffer; adapter chooses the injection point.
end note

VRC -> RP : AddCommandBuffer(camera, cameraEvent, commandBuffer)
activate RP
note right of RP
  UrpRenderPipeline:
    RenderPassEvent.BeforeRenderingOpaques
    via ScriptableRenderFeature
  HdrpRenderPipeline:
    RenderPipelineManager.beginCameraRendering
    via CustomPass injection
  NullRenderPipeline (tests): no-op
end note
RP --> VRC : <size:9>(render pass enqueued)</size>
deactivate RP

deactivate VRC
VRB --> Unity
deactivate VRB

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  STEP 8 — GPU executes ray-march (outside domain code)
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
note over Unity
  <b>Step 8 — GPU executes ray-march shader</b>
  CommandBuffer dispatched by render pipeline at the registered camera event.
  VolumeRaymarch.shader reads uniforms set in Step 6:
    • ray steps determined by _StepsLow / _StepsHigh + _FovStart / _FovEnd
    • voxel colours from dataCube Texture3D (FilterMode.Point — nearest-neighbour)
    • masked voxels handled by active _MASK_* keyword
  Pixels composited on screen.
  <b>≥ 90 fps invariant (INV-01): steps 1–7 are O(1) CPU work.</b>
  GPU workload is unchanged from before; only the CPU dispatch path changes.
end note

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  PERFORMANCE CONTRACT
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
note over VRB, RP
  <b>Performance contract</b>
  Steps 1–7: CPU-side value-type copies and uniform pushes — O(1), no per-frame heap allocation.
  Step 5 texture upload: triggered by data change only (not every frame); < 2 ms spike (CI gate).
  Step 6 shader sync: single Tick() call replaces 25+ scattered SetFloat/SetInt calls in VDSR.Update().
  CK improvement: WMC 97 → ≤ 12 per class; CBO 45 → ≤ 11 per domain class; LCOM 0.81 → ≤ 0.05.
end note

@enduml
